THE SECRET SAUCE:

PARTIAL COMPLETION

You NEVER want most people to fully complete everything.

Why?

Because incompletion creates return gravity.

People revisit because:

“I’m only missing three Johto entries.”

That’s incredibly powerful psychologically.

⸻

THE PARK SHOULD FEEL ENDLESS

Even if physically finite.

Ways to do this:

* rotating Pokémon
* randomized encounters
* seasonal migrations
* nighttime-only events
* hidden rooms
* evolving AI behaviors
* rare encounter probabilities

You want:

“I wonder what I’ll discover this time.”

Every visit.

⸻

THE SOCIAL FLEX LAYER

Another huge missing component.

People LOVE signaling:

* rarity
* dedication
* expertise
* insider knowledge

So:

* exclusive badges
* hard-to-find Pokémon
* rare titles
* legendary encounters
* hidden collectibles

become social currency.

Guests become walking stories.

⸻

THE “DISCOVERY ENGINE”

The best version creates constant:
small discoveries.

Examples:

* hidden sounds
* secret pathways
* NPC hints
* environmental storytelling
* rare encounters
* hidden merch
* easter eggs

Your brain starts scanning the environment constantly.

That’s immersion.

⸻

THE KEY:

THE PARK SHOULD REWARD CURIOSITY

Not just spending.

That’s what makes it magical instead of predatory.

People should feel:

“The world gives back when I pay attention.”

That’s the emotional structure behind great exploration games.

